{"TopicId":180592,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Rocket lens flares?","CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-14T18:37:28Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-14T18:37:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/rFDh3E6wxx8?start=21\u0026amp;feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo any mods give us lens flares on rocket engines?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have scatterer, Real Plume, and Engine Lighting, but none of them give the dramatic flare effect on the engines (scatterer only works on the sun).\u003Cbr\u003E\nHas anybody figured out a way to do this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shadowmage","CreatedById":138730,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-14T21:25:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn theory it wouldn\u0027t be that \u0027hard\u0027 to add lens-flares to engines, at least in a naive/basic fashion.\u00A0 I\u0027m not currently aware of any mods that do this however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst, create a lens-flare asset in Unity Editor.\u00A0 Export the .flare \u002B textures to an asset bundle.\u00A0 Load this asset bundle into KSP through custom plugin code.\u00A0 Create a new PartModule to manage your lens-flare for specific parts; patch this module onto engines.\u00A0 In the new module, add the lens-flare component to the engines primary transform, and use the plugin to manipulate the flares \u0027contribution\u0027/visibility based on the engines\u0027 current thrust setting/thrust output.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nObv. it would need to be quite a bit more complex than the simple implementation I outlined in order to handle edge-cases and add some optimizations (e.g. you don\u0027t want 27 lens flares showing for a \u0027cluster\u0027 of engines, but only one), but I think that in theory it is entirely doable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mecripp","CreatedById":181994,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T01:24:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed8159848325\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/106089-15x-cryogenic-engines-high-isp-chemical-rockets-november-5/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHad a FX close to that when it started out but think they got changed, I think it was just two FX running at same time\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-12-15T15:31:05Z\u0022 title=\u002212/15/2018 03:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 15, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Mecripp\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T05:03:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138730-shadowmage/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022138730\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/138730-shadowmage/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Shadowmage\u003C/a\u003E, I had this question after messing around in SSTU trying to make a Delta IV heavy (inspired by this week\u0027s launch) and wondering if I could use Real Plume to make the fireball that occurs at the launch of that rocket.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181994-mecripp/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022181994\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/181994-mecripp/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Mecripp\u003C/a\u003E, interesting, I just peaked at\u00A0the Cryogenic Engines configs and it has an outdated config for the Engine Light mod (module name changed). I\u0027m going to try to swap the module names and see what \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002283952\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/83952-nertea/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nertea\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0came up with.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt looks like CryoEngines has an outdated config for Engine Light that actually prevents the mod from loading properly. I\u00A0went ahead and submitted a fix for Cryo Engines over on github.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://github.com/ChrisAdderley/CryoEngines/issues/46\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://github.com/ChrisAdderley/CryoEngines/issues/46\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-12-15T05:04:04Z\u0022 title=\u002212/15/2018 05:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 15, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Nightside\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mecripp","CreatedById":181994,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T15:36:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150244-nightside/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022150244\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/150244-nightside/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Nightside\u003C/a\u003E One might try to add a 2nd transformer where the thrust transformer is and name it Sun or might even change the name to Sun and see what happens ? If scatter will show the Sun fare on it\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-23T00:37:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell it seems like the capability to have awesome flares is mostly exists already with a combination of RealPlume/smokescreen\u00A0and EngineLight.\u00A0However Realplume configs just haven\u0027t been totally awesomized\u00A0for massive flares.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nI actually tried to use one of\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167617\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167617-jadeofmaar/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@JadeOfMaar\u003C/a\u003E\u0027s sun flares with RealPlume, but the that requires a .mu, while the sun flares for scatterer are textures.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, I messed with the configs (Bigger and Brighter obviously) and got some pretty good looking stuff.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot16\u0022 src=\u0022https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20480557/50379702-53150380-0605-11e9-9305-789a16eb3441.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cb\u003E\u003Cu\u003EWaiting until dark to launch\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/b\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot17\u0022 src=\u0022https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20480557/50379703-54463080-0605-11e9-99f5-fc078bc0f5a5.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cu\u003EIgnition...\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot18\u0022 src=\u0022https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20480557/50379704-560ff400-0605-11e9-91b0-e19c6bf40784.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cu\u003ELiftoff!\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022screenshot24\u0022 src=\u0022https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/20480557/50379727-e0f0ee80-0605-11e9-8731-485e9e2c2023.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cu\u003EInto the void\u003C/u\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mecripp","CreatedById":181994,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-23T17:52:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223509723\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180592\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221545525456\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150244\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Nightside\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 hours ago, Nightside said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell it seems like the capability to have awesome flares is mostly exists already with a combination of RealPlume/smokescreen\u00A0and EngineLight.\u00A0However Realplume configs just haven\u0027t been totally awesomized\u00A0for massive flares.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nI actually tried to use one of\u00A0\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile